  "original_title": "\u0db4\u0ddc\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0dca \u0db1\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0db0\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dd3\u0db1\u0dca\u0d9c\u0dda \u0dc3\u0dd4\u0db6 \u0dc3\u0dcf\u0db0\u0db1\u0dba \u0db4\u0dd4\u0dc5\u0dd4\u0dbd\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dd9\u0dbb\u0dda",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The welfare of police officers will be expanded",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Ministry of Public Security has stated in a statement that the Cabinet has approved to increase the monthly travel allowance currently paid to police officers.",
        "Accordingly, the current monthly travel allowance will be increased from 14 to 21 days and the payment will be made from January 1, 2023.",
        "It is stated in the announcement that the cabinet also approved the establishment of a legal aid fund for the legal matters faced by the police officers in the performance of their duties.",
        "This fund is managed by a committee headed by the Inspector General of Police and on the recommendations of the said committee, legal aid can be obtained by all the police officers and in case of need, the assistance of the President's Bar Panel can also be obtained.",
        "In the announcement, the condition of vehicle ownership to the concerned police officer or the officer's spouse has been removed in the supply of vehicles to higher positions from the position of Assistant Superintendent of Police and the previous permission for 15-year-old vehicles was also given permission for 20-year-old vehicles on the recommendation of the technical engineer of the police garage. It is further mentioned."
      ],
